  "why": "The paper demonstrates cross-model transferability of the discovered fault-inducing inputs (over-refusal queries) but does not incorporate explicit mechanisms within the fuzzing design to discover them. The fuzzing framework, ORFUZZ, is designed to find over-refusals for a single target model at a time. The authors then conduct a separate, post-hoc analysis (RQ4) to assess the transferability of the generated samples across other models. They generate inputs for five initial models and then test how well these inputs transfer to the others. Based on the most transferable samples, they create a new benchmark dataset, ORFUZZSET, and evaluate its effectiveness on an expanded set of 14 different LLMs. This post-hoc demonstration of transferability without explicit design mechanisms for it fits the 'Medium' rating.",
